## 12. **FAILURE PROTOCOL** ğŸš¨ **MANDATORY**

### **If ANY Compilation Error:**
```
1. ğŸ›‘ STOP ALL DEVELOPMENT immediately
2. ğŸ” Identify the root cause of the error
3. ğŸ”§ Fix the compilation error completely
4. ğŸ§ª Re-run ENTIRE verification suite
5. ğŸ“ Document the fix and prevention
6. âœ… Only proceed when ALL verifications pass
```

### **If ANY Warning:**
```
1. ğŸ›‘ STOP and address the warning
2. ğŸ“Š Determine if warning indicates real issue
3. ğŸ”§ Fix the underlying problem OR add explicit allow
4. ğŸ§ª Verify warning is resolved
5. ğŸ“ Document why allow was added (if applicable)
```

### **If ANY Test Failure:**
```
1. ğŸ›‘ STOP and investigate test failure
2. ğŸ” Determine if test or code is incorrect
3. ğŸ”§ Fix the failing functionality
4. ğŸ§ª Ensure ALL tests pass
5. ğŸ“ˆ Add additional tests if coverage gaps found
```

